vs-earth-map-creator-O
============================
Make cool earth maps in Vintage Story (VS)

Original code by tlm9201. Heavily modified and improved, and the bash script image processing pipeline was rewritten in python for windows+linux compat and ease of use.
Not a fork because its functionally impossible to pull from upstream (due to the extent of rewrite) and the merge conflicts got annoying.

https://github.com/tlm9201/vs-earth-map-creator

Requirements
-------------------
dotnet 8
vintage story
python3 (+ pip packages, see Geo/requirements.txt)
ImageMagick (optional, for river post-processing — falls back to Pillow if absent)

Directories
-------------------
.
├── CakeBuild         - build
├── EarthMapCreator   - vs code mod
└── Geo               - geospatial processing scripts

Python Pipeline (Geo/)
-------------------
The pipeline downloads some datasets automatically, but several large files must be
placed manually in Geo/datasets/ before running:

  ds75_grd.zip              GMTED 250m DEM (topography)
                            https://edcintl.cr.usgs.gov/downloads/sciweb1/shared/topo/downloads/GMTED/Grid_ZipFiles/ds75_grd.zip

  gebco_2025_sub_ice_topo.zip  GEBCO bathymetry (or extract the .nc and place it directly)
                            https://www.gebco.net/data_and_products/gridded_bathymetry_data/

  ne_10m_rivers_lake_centerlines.zip  Natural Earth rivers
                            https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/

  ne_10m_lakes.zip          Natural Earth lakes
                            https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/

  gm_ve_v1.zip              Global vegetation canopy cover
                            https://www.earthenv.org/vegetation

The following are downloaded automatically on first run:
  - OSM land polygons
  - Köppen-Geiger climate classification

Once datasets are in place:

  0. The python scripts work on Windows or Linux, but you must have python and pip installed.

  1. Install Python dependencies:
       cd Geo/
       pip install -r requirements.txt

  2. Edit Geo/config.py to set your bounding box (LAT_MIN/MAX, LON_MIN/MAX),
     output resolution (FINAL_WIDTH, FINAL_LENGTH — must be multiples of 512),
     and projection. You can use sites such as https://boundingbox.klokantech.com/
	 to find a bounding box for the desired map.

  3. Run the pipeline:
       python launch.py

  4. Output PNGs will be written to Geo/work/build/.

Usage (in Vintage Story)
-------------------
1. Copy all PNGs from Geo/work/build/ into your VS data directory:
     Linux:   ~/.config/VintagestoryData/EarthMap/
     Windows: %APPDATA%\VintagestoryData\EarthMap\

2. Set MapWidthBlocks and MapHeightBlocks in:
     ModConfig/EarthMapCreator.json
   to match the FINAL_WIDTH and FINAL_LENGTH you used in config.py.

3. Install the mod, create a new world (ideally with the same dimensions as your generated map images), and the mod should begin generating chunks based on the earth map data.

   The map is placed so that chunk 0,0 (top-left of the world) aligns with
   the top-left of your PNG images. Map size must be a multiple of 512 blocks.
   If you create a world that is larger than the generated images, you may spawn in the void since the entire area outside the valid image data zone is simply not generated.
   Vintage story spawns you in the center of the total map dimensions and maps in-game coordinates to that center.

Limitations
-------------------
- Map generation must be a multiple of 512 blocks.
- Maximum 256 height.
- Much more data could be applied to VS (rock strata, ores, hot springs, etc.)
- Vintage Story map resolutions/padding are hardcoded on the client.

